MISSION — "polylogue feels instant and knows where you left off"
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Three beads forming one coherent UX arc, in this order:
  1. polylogue-20d.1  — CLI→daemon fast path over UDS (persistent hot process)
  2. polylogue-jnj.13 — bare-invocation triage (status + 5 recent sessions)
  3. polylogue-37t.8  — resume routing: session → harness reopen command

Why together: 20d.1 makes every read instant; jnj.13 makes the instant thing
you see on bare `polylogue` be "here's where you left off"; 37t.8 makes
"continue" actually reopen the session. Ship order matters: 20d.1 first (the
other two ride on its speed), jnj.13 second (composes existing pieces),
37t.8 third (greenfield module). One PR per bead is allowed and preferred if
each is coherent; a single 3-commit-series PR is acceptable if you finish all
three — decide by size when you get there.

