BEAD 2: polylogue-jnj.13 — bare-invocation triage
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Bare `polylogue` (no args, on a tty) currently shows Click help. Target: an
inviting triage surface instead —
  - archive status one-liner (daemon fresh? converged? — the health probe
    from 20d.1 gives you this nearly free),
  - the five most recent sessions (id, origin, title, age) — the select
    renderer already produces exactly these rows; this is COMPOSITION of
    existing pieces, not new rendering,
  - the three most useful next commands (e.g. `polylogue find …`,
    `polylogue read <id>`, `polylogue continue <id>`).
CONSTRAINTS:
  - <200ms budget: one indexed query, NO insight loads. Ride the 20d.1 fast
    path when the daemon is up; direct-but-minimal when not.
  - Non-tty (machine mode) output UNCHANGED. Strict command floor (#1842)
    behavior UNCHANGED: `polylogue foo` (bare unquoted word) must still raise
    the UsageError with did-you-mean — see cli/query_group.py
    _looks_like_query_expression/_bare_root_error_message. Do not regress
    tests/unit/cli around the floor.
  - No archive at all → current help text fallback.
AC verify: devtools test -k bare + a timing spot-check recorded in the PR.
GOTCHA: any new Click params on query verbs go LAST (positional-shift bug).

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
BEAD 3: polylogue-37t.8 — resume routing (the continue verb's last mile)
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Nothing owns "reopen this session in its harness." Build:
  - A resume-routing helper mapping (origin, native_session_id) → concrete
    reopen command: Claude Code → `claude --resume <native_id>`; Codex →
    `codex resume <native_id>` (interactive TUI; `codex exec resume <id>`
    is the headless variant — pick the interactive one for a human-facing
    continue, note both in code). Cover at least these two; every other
    origin returns an explicit typed unsupported/unknown result — NEVER
    a guessed command.
  - Session cwd matters: Claude Code sessions are per-project — the reopen
    command should include (or print) the session's working directory when
    the archive knows it (sessions carry workspace/repo metadata — check
    what the schema actually stores before promising it).
  - Wire into the `continue` verb: `find … then continue` (and
    `polylogue continue <id>`) ends with the reopen command EMITTED by
    default (print the exact command); optionally EXECUTED behind an
    explicit flag (--exec). Emitting is the safe default — the CLI may be
    running in contexts where spawning a TUI is wrong.
  - Already-open detection (kitty/hyprland control plane) goes behind a
    pluggable interface (e.g. a protocol with a null default impl) —
    OPTIONAL, degrade cleanly, NO hard dependency on kitty/hyprland, and do
    NOT import sinnix-specific paths in polylogue/ core. If you implement a
    sinnix probe, put it behind an env-gated entry point and keep tests
    dependency-free.
AC verify: devtools test on the routing module asserting per-origin command
mapping for fixture sessions (Claude Code, Codex, and an unsupported origin);
manual `continue` on one real Claude and one real Codex session recorded in
the PR body.

