VERIFICATION DISCIPLINE (worker-owned)
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- Inner loop: `devtools test <exact files>` / `-k <expr>` — NEVER blanket
  directories. `devtools verify --quick` before every push (pre-push runs it
  anyway; running it yourself avoids surprise rejections).
- Anti-vacuity: for each new test, state in the PR which production
  dependency it enters and which implementation mutation would make it fail.
  Toy replicas and mocks that only prove their own wiring are rejected.
- The daemon for live testing: `polylogued run --no-api` variants conflict
  with the LIVE daemon on this host — for integration-ish tests use the
  workspace_env fixture + a DaemonAPIHTTPServer started in-test (see
  tests/visual/test_reader_semantic_cards.py for the pattern) — NEVER touch
  /realm/data/... or the live archive root.
- Timing claims: measure on the demo corpus, report the exact commands +
  numbers in the PR. If the live-archive numbers differ, say so honestly.

KNOWN HAZARDS (all live tonight):
- GitHub Actions fails ALL jobs at init with no steps (account billing
  lock) — infra, not your diff; ignore that pattern, do not chase it.
- devtools test basetemp can escape to host /tmp from worktrees
  (polylogue-ra3w, another lane is fixing it) — pass an explicit
  basetemp/tmp override under /realm/tmp for anything heavy.
- bd prints "auto-importing ... into empty database" noise per invocation
  (polylogue-gxjh) — harmless for reads; SEQUENCE your bd calls; do not
  parallel-mutate beads.
- Pre-commit hook runs ruff format+lint + bd export; if it rejects, fix and
  make a NEW commit (never --amend a successful one, never --no-verify).

